This issue is **not** related to Artifactory. 

It was because there was a reference to http://jcenter.bintray.com in the pom file. 

    &lt;repository&gt;
       &lt;id&gt;bintray-central&lt;/id&gt;
       &lt;name&gt;bintray&lt;/name&gt;
       &lt;url&gt;https://jcenter.bintray.com&lt;/url&gt;
    &lt;/repository&gt;

I am not sure why it did not fail earlier. I am assuming there has been a recent change in the jcenter.bintray.com site to redirect all calls for http to https with a 302. 
Changing the bintray URL to https, like this, deleting the old files in .m2 folder and rebuilding resolved the issue.

    &lt;!-- Updated http url --&gt;
    &lt;repository&gt;
       &lt;id&gt;bintray-central&lt;/id&gt;
       &lt;name&gt;bintray&lt;/name&gt;
       &lt;url&gt;https://jcenter.bintray.com&lt;/url&gt;
    &lt;/repository&gt;

